Dialogue: 10,0:00:07.34,0:00:12.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I left my lodgings as soon as Porcupine told me to go. {yamaarashi}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:12.61,0:00:17.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But I had nowhere to go, so I continued to wander around the town.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:18.16,0:00:20.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Slowly, the sky turned to twilight.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.18,0:00:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the Kajiya district?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:42.29,0:00:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's mostly ancestral mansions. {of clans}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:45.36,0:00:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they probably won't be renting rooms.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:48.88,0:00:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah! \NUnprepared lives in this area. {uranari}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:53.07,0:00:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's just terrible!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:55.95,0:00:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It is. Do you perhaps know of anyone around here who's looking
Dialogue: 10,0:00:59.32,0:01:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,for a boarder or could just let me stay for a night?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:01.95,0:01:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm, well...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:05.13,0:01:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, right!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:06.49,0:01:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an elderly couple named Hagino living behind us.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:09.71,0:01:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They told me they'd rent out their vacant tatami room to someone trustworthy.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:13.59,0:01:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Much obliged!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:20.18,0:01:24.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Unprepared, I became a resident at the Hagino house that night.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:26.06,0:01:28.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After that, I didn't speak to Porcupine at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:32.23,0:01:35.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A meeting was held to decide\N the punishment for the boarding students
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.82,0:01:38.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,who pulled my leg \Nthe other night while on night duty.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:39.75,0:01:42.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Obviously, this was entirely their fault.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:42.74,0:01:46.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I was certain that everyone would demand strict punishment, but I was wrong.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:47.42,0:01:53.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Red Shirt, Buffoon, and the others\Nsuggested leniency.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:53.74,0:01:57.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I got more and more furious \Nand decided to voice a protest.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.29,0:02:01.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But just as I was about to speak up, \NPorcupine stood up first. {lit: half-lifted my ass off the chair}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:02.68,0:02:06.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He was... the one who incited the students to begin with.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.46,0:02:08.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I already know he'd be lenient\N like the others.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.62,0:02:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't disagree more with what\N the vice principal and others have just said.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.82,0:02:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how you look at it,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.82,0:02:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,this incident was obviously fifty of our students conspiring
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.40,0:02:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to humiliate a rookie teacher.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:23.19,0:02:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The vice principal suggests that the fault lies with said teacher's character.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:27.89,0:02:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,With all due respect, \NI think that's inappropriate.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:30.63,0:02:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He was put on night duty \Nafter less than 20 days on the job.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.55,0:02:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The students couldn't possibly have had time to evaluate his scholarly
Dialogue: 10,0:02:39.31,0:02:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,or personal character\N in such a short period.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.09,0:02:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Without any provocation, \Nthey chose to ridicule and dishonor him.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.68,0:02:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If we let such a conduct
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.46,0:02:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,from students slide, \Nit will affect the school's reputation.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:51.65,0:02:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to ask for a harsh punishment for all the students.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.65,0:02:56.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I was shocked.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.44,0:02:59.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He agreed completely with me.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.26,0:03:05.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But why would the instigator call for punishment of his own accomplices?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.87,0:03:08.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Maybe Red Shirt was the real liar.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.58,0:03:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In conclusion, I kindly request
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.34,0:03:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that you approach this matter with the utmost seriousness.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.67,0:03:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one detail I forgot to mention.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.85,0:03:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That night, the teacher on night duty
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.45,0:03:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,left the school to go to the springs.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.52,0:03:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I find that behavior outrageous.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:29.89,0:03:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Punishment for students aside, \NI believe the principal should also
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.00,0:03:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,take disciplinary action against the teacher in question.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.90,0:03:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I admit it. I {\i1}did{\i0} go\N to the hot springs that night.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.78,0:03:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wrong, and I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.48,0:03:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Koga, what did you think\N about the vice principal's speech?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.93,0:04:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When he said teachers occupy\N an elevated position in society?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.65,0:04:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,"Spurn all worldly pleasures."
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.69,0:04:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning you can't go\N for soba or dumplings. {dango}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.55,0:04:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, you should fish, \Nread literature, and write poetry. {haiku}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.35,0:04:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And that teachers should only seek spiritual pleasures.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.64,0:04:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he really say that?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.63,0:04:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Weren't you listening?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.91,0:04:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but I had something else on my mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.71,0:04:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, tasty dumplings and tempura soba {\i1}are{\i0} a spiritual pleasure!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.75,0:04:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The vice principal's got some nerve,\N talking like that,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.92,0:04:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,when he's sneaking out to meet \Na geisha named Madonna himself.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.51,0:04:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:36.91,0:04:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.52,0:04:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no geisha named Madonna?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.95,0:04:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.10,0:04:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,"Madonna" is a foreign word,\N meaning "beautiful woman."
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.18,0:04:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:54.35,0:04:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Then maybe it's somebody's nickname?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.69,0:04:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it refers to Miss Toyama.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.39,0:05:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Your friend, Koga, who brought you here, was engaged to her.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.44,0:05:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All the arrangements had been made.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.74,0:05:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But sadly, Koga's father\N passed away last year.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.77,0:05:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, a lot more has happened,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:15.32,0:05:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and his family has found themselves in reduced circumstances.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.99,0:05:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a fine young man, \Nbut he's often taken advantage of.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.18,0:05:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,For one reason or the other, \Nthe wedding kept getting postponed.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.22,0:05:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the vice principal jumped the gun and proposed to her.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.35,0:05:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So that's what it was.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.17,0:05:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Red Shirt is just a treacherous viper!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.06,0:05:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Toyama also felt obliged to Koga, {debt of gratitude; social obligation}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:39.34,0:05:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so she didn't accept \Nhis proposal right away.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.10,0:05:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But the vice principal persisted.\N He wanted the Toyama's status.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.13,0:05:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, at last, \Nhe succeeded in taming her.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.43,0:05:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,One two-way ticket for the hot springs.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.01,0:06:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Koga, are you going to the hot springs?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.94,0:06:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.63,0:06:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think I have to apologize to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:10.55,0:06:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know all the circumstances, \Nso my joke about the geisha...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.66,0:06:32.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,Madonna really is beautiful.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.66,0:06:35.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm no good at describing what makes a woman gorgeous,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.55,0:06:36.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,so I won't try. {from the book TL}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.97,0:06:40.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,Looking at her made me feel like I was cradling a ball of crystal
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.19,0:06:42.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,that had been warmed in perfume in my palm. {also from the book}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.05,0:06:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:54.18,0:06:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd be late, \Nso I was in an awful rush,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.02,0:07:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but I still have several minutes.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.00,0:07:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You must really like hot springs.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.40,0:07:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. They're great. They're the only good thing about this place.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.41,0:07:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no. I know you can't really mean that.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.45,0:07:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not from this area either,\N but this is a good town.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:21.41,0:07:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've lived here a while, \Nyou'll grow to see it too.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.04,0:07:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, the train's finally here.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.11,0:07:33.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I didn't see Red Shirt at the hot springs.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.81,0:07:36.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,There were many baths,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.30,0:07:39.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,so I didn't expect to run into him\N for a second time in one night. {lit: after taking the same train, it was unlikely we take the same bathhouse too}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.93,0:07:43.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The moon was beautiful when I left the bath,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.54,0:07:45.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,so l decided to walk home.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.62,0:08:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If we just wait a little while, \Neverything will resolve itself.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.14,0:08:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How long is "a while"?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.22,0:08:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, about six months maybe?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.65,0:08:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's too long. I hate waiting.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.34,0:08:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, then three months.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.01,0:08:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,One month.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.36,0:08:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I can't do that! \NThat's way too soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.79,0:08:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's head home now.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.12,0:08:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:26.62,0:08:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's getting late.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.08,0:08:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I've decided to let you treat me\N to shaved ice, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.09,0:08:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.47,0:08:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I'm afraid \NI have to apologize to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:57.04,0:08:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Apologize?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.19,0:09:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, for believing your landlord.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.40,0:09:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I checked up on his story.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.51,0:09:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He told lies about you \Nbecause you wouldn't buy his antiques.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.03,0:09:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you forgive me?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.01,0:09:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:14.44,0:09:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, have you heard?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.63,0:09:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.75,0:09:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Koga's been transferred.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.37,0:09:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.42,0:09:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So Red Shirt has finally managed \Nto chase him off.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.47,0:09:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Koga's a good man. Maybe too good.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.24,0:09:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's rough up Red Shirt \Nat the farewell party.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.87,0:09:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't! We'd just make more trouble for Koga.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.32,0:09:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're going to rough Red Shirt up, \Nwe'll have to catch him
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.77,0:09:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,red-handed at one of his schemes.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:47.56,0:09:49.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At Unprepared's farewell party,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.36,0:09:51.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the vice principal stood up \Nafter the principal.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:51.46,0:09:53.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He showered Unprepared in feigned praise.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.86,0:09:57.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He even said that to lose \Nsuch a good man
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.20,0:10:00.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was a personal tragedy \Nthat left him in deep sorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.20,0:10:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Previously, Principal and Vice Principal\Ncalled Koga's departure a tragedy.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:10.81,0:10:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I completely disagree.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.30,0:10:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that Koga can escape\N from here as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.37,0:10:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The town that he will be moving to
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.26,0:10:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,may be less materially convenient than where we are now,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.52,0:10:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but I hear it's a place \Nof remarkably simple customs.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.01,0:10:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt there'd be even a single smooth-talking dandy there,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.63,0:10:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,who'd shower Koga in praise through his teeth,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.46,0:10:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,or a vain beauty who will manipulate our trusting friend.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.03,0:10:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they'll recognize Koga for the gentleman he is
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.74,0:10:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and welcome him with open arms.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.89,0:10:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I congratulate him\N on his future good fortune.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.86,0:11:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know that Red Shirt has been seeing a geisha?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:06.35,0:11:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:08.52,0:11:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She was at Koga's farewell party.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.46,0:11:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're pretty sharp.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.48,0:11:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When she arrived,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.05,0:11:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Red Shirt completely ignored her\N and walked right past her when he left.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.12,0:11:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't stop at anything in his schemes!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.93,0:11:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand him!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.71,0:11:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Damn right.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.03,0:11:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"Smooth-talking dandy" back then\N wasn't strong enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.88,0:11:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what {\i1}should{\i0} I have said?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.26,0:11:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have called him a loathsome,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.16,0:11:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,slimy, lying, twisted, festering, pathetic little dandy! {not gonna check all of this >_>; buncha fancy words}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:40.73,0:11:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not that good with words.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.12,0:11:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,With a vocabulary like that,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.13,0:11:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,why don't you give more speeches?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.56,0:11:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No... My vocabulary's no good \Nfor speeches, only for arguments.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.86,0:11:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of that, this morning,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.97,0:11:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,my students almost had a fight\N with students from the normal school. {shihan gakkou = teachers' training college; book: According to what I was told, the students in middle schools and normal schools in any provincial town fight like cats and dogs.}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.12,0:12:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Middle schools and normal schools are always like cats and dogs.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.49,0:12:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... Well, then, with all the meat gone,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.80,0:12:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I could use a walk to help settle my meal.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.87,0:12:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, good idea.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.71,0:12:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.36,0:12:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher! This is big!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.17,0:12:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.26,0:12:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a fight with the normal school!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.29,0:12:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So it finally happened?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.17,0:12:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Please hurry!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.03,0:12:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. Where are they fighting?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.51,0:12:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,On the riverbed!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.08,0:12:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher, hurry!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.48,0:12:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It figures. {lit: those brats are impossible}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:29.78,0:12:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't just stand here and do nothing. Let's go!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.44,0:12:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We must end this \Nbefore the police arrive. {??? can't hear}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.95,0:12:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.86,0:12:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, just break them up.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.37,0:12:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.95,0:12:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Break it up! Enough!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.88,0:12:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you, stop it!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.95,0:12:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Stop fighting!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.33,0:12:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.37,0:12:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop with the violence!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.79,0:12:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You are disgracing your school! Disperse!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.87,0:12:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.93,0:13:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now their teachers are helping!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.08,0:13:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They're too big to beat like that. Use rocks!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.52,0:13:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Behave yourselves! Stop fighting!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.56,0:13:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the police! Run!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.20,0:13:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This newspaper story \Nis a total fabrication!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.78,0:13:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hotta and I didn't start the fight.\N We tried to stop it!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.50,0:13:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just unforgivable!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.12,0:13:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,"A certain impudent new teacher, just transferred from Tokyo..."
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.09,0:13:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They should at least use my name!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:39.21,0:13:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, don't get worked up.\N Your bruises are still fresh. {lit: your body hurts doesn't it}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.91,0:13:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to complain to the paper!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.73,0:13:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you come with me?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.60,0:13:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me take care\N of this newspaper affair.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.06,0:13:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll see that they print a retraction.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.93,0:13:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, thank you. I'll go alone.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.44,0:13:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get in a row with the editor,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.05,0:14:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the next story will be even worse, \Ninstead of a retraction.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.90,0:14:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let me handle this, okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:05.67,0:14:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.05,0:14:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This article is utter nonsense!\N Principal, you must believe me.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.37,0:14:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. By the way, \Nwhy don't you two take a day off?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.23,0:14:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, thank you, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.80,0:14:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The article was printed\N at Red Shirt's request.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.67,0:14:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Can he really do that?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.78,0:14:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You bet he can.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.24,0:14:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll probably be dismissed. {dismissal; sacking; discharge}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.99,0:14:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Only if we slip up one more time.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.98,0:14:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here's my class.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.57,0:14:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet down! \NHey! I said be quiet!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.26,0:14:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit! There's no retraction!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.29,0:14:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you want\N my resignation too?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.55,0:15:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you ask Hotta\N to resign, but not me?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.43,0:15:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The school has its reasons.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.34,0:15:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Those reasons are wrong.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.68,0:15:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should Hotta resign, while I...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.84,0:15:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you're quite right.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.47,0:15:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hotta's dismissal was unavoidable.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.48,0:15:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We did not see any need\N to sack you as well, however.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.05,0:15:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me. {/I'm coming in}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:34.62,0:15:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How are things at school?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.08,0:15:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Same as always.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.37,0:15:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Does anyone suspect I stayed behind\N on the second floor of Masuya?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.17,0:15:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They all think you've long\N gone home to Aizu.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.89,0:15:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all Red Shirt's fault.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:48.05,0:15:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Just looking at his face makes me want to vomit, yet I can't tell him!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.24,0:15:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to go back to Tokyo. {/want to quit and ... sooner}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.72,0:15:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we punish him,\N we can both go home.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.68,0:16:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I can give them my resignation any day, now.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.02,0:16:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Will Red Shirt really visit that inn?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.85,0:16:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. He'll come!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.78,0:16:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How many days have we been waiting?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:08.58,0:16:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven days.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.24,0:16:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.74,0:16:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been staying out \N especially late recently.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.52,0:16:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.05,0:16:34.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,She's here.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.36,0:16:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They're finally here.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:41.97,0:16:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Kosuzu and another geisha \Narrived around 7:30.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.39,0:16:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Was Red Shirt with them?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.52,0:16:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:47.74,0:16:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this is pointless.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.53,0:16:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Two geisha is actually good news for us.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.45,0:16:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:53.57,0:16:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Red Shirt's a tricky bastard. \NHe'll try to sneak in later.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.12,0:17:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You might be right, \Nbut isn't it already after nine?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.04,0:17:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 9:12.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.14,0:17:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, extinguish the lamp.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.63,0:17:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If that fox sees our silhouettes up here, then the plan's blown.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.72,0:17:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm giving up if they don't come tonight.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.79,0:17:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll stay until my money runs out.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.07,0:17:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like they won't show up tonight, either.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.10,0:17:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There they are!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.04,0:18:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while, so I'm excited!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.68,0:18:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They're out of our way now,\N and everything's settled down again.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:05.33,0:18:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They had plenty of energy, \Nbut no plan.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:07.69,0:18:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I must say, the kid's such a Tokyo fool! {https://jisho.org/word/%E3%81%B9%E3%82%89%E3%82%93%E3%82%81%E3%81%88}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:10.53,0:18:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for a Tokyo fool, he still has the gallantry of a botchan,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.15,0:18:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so there's certain charm to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.69,0:18:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have seen him when he tried to resign.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:16.87,0:18:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I could hardly hold back from laughing.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.37,0:18:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true! Very true!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.53,0:18:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Those bastards!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.13,0:18:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They've finally shown their true colors.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.21,0:18:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's rush into Kadoya now \Nand catch them at the scene!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.33,0:18:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No! We can't.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:33.54,0:18:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If we force our way in,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.83,0:18:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the innkeeper will have us\N arrested for assault.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.88,0:18:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we knock, \Nthey'll escape out the back door.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.61,0:18:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we'll just have to wait \Nfor them to come out.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.51,0:19:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.45,0:19:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hotta!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.85,0:19:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what was our vice principal doing all night at the Kadoya Inn?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.95,0:19:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I forbidden from staying\N at an inn because of my position?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.27,0:19:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It is forbidden for you to see a geisha!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:33.27,0:19:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you prove that I brought a geisha with me?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.36,0:19:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up! You called me\N a foolish Tokyo botchan! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.94,0:19:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I wasn't talking about you!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.45,0:19:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, a liar!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.44,0:19:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The two of us just stayed\N there for the night. {me and yoshikawa}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.59,0:19:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Some geisha came at 7:30, \Nbut we never met them.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.65,0:19:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.89,0:19:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough talk! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.66,0:19:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-This is assault. {violence}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.92,0:20:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's against the law to hit someone because of your suspicions! {???????? nc what's there in the beginning}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.01,0:20:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care about the law!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.28,0:20:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A beating is the only answer I've got for scum like you!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.72,0:20:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.25,0:20:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this!{kurae}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:15.77,0:20:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How about this?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.41,0:20:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You're out of your mind! \NS-Save me! Please!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.57,0:20:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You two are nothing but crooks!\N Consider this your divine punishment.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.68,0:20:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn from this and reflect! {???????}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:27.58,0:20:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Say what you want, \Nbut justice will prevail in the end.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.66,0:20:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to run or hide. \NI'll be down at the harbor until 5 PM.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.46,0:20:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Come find me. \NBring the police or whatever!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.88,0:20:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be there too!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.30,0:20:45.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I checked out of my lodgings\N and went down to the harbor.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.64,0:20:49.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,We waited until 6 PM, but nobody showed up, not even the police.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:50.46,0:20:54.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At sunset, Porcupine and I sailed away from this town.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:07.51,0:21:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiyo!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:10.02,0:21:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiyo!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.02,0:21:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,B-Botchan!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.00,0:21:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiyo!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.87,0:21:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiyo, how are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:17.25,0:21:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you sure came back rather early.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.77,0:21:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never go to the country again.\N I'll stay in Tokyo with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.84,0:21:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Botchan...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.61,0:21:35.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A friend was able to get me \Na job as a streetcar conductor. {assistant engineer}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:36.41,0:21:39.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The salary was 25 yen a month. \NOur rent was only 6 yen.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:39.87,0:21:44.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Our house wasn't very large, \Nbut Kiyo was happy with it.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:44.53,0:21:49.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Sadly, Kiyo caught pneumonia and passed away this past February.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.74,0:21:52.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The day before she died, \Nshe called out to me:
Dialogue: 10,0:21:53.34,0:21:54.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"Botchan,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:54.88,0:21:58.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,after I die, bury me in your temple." {??? obviously he doesn't own a temple so idk what this means}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:58.69,0:22:03.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"I'll wait for you there \Nuntil we can be reunited."
Dialogue: 10,0:22:14.35,0:22:19.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,So I buried Kiyo \Nat the Ryogen temple in Kohinata.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.78,0:22:37.39,Song,,0,0,0,,I write a letter to my loved one
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.39,0:22:44.58,Song,,0,0,0,,I write and tear it, tear it, and write again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.58,0:22:51.15,Song,,0,0,0,,I throw the rolled up paper at the window {meaning at the glass, probably as a distraction}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.15,0:22:58.13,Song,,0,0,0,,It's raining outside, just like the tears on my cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.40,0:23:06.23,Song,,0,0,0,,Life is a sea, youth is a boat
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.23,0:23:13.27,Song,,0,0,0,,My love, please come and save me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.27,0:23:15.41,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.57,0:23:19.45,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.45,0:23:27.04,Song,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm sinking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.04,0:23:36.48,Song,,0,0,0,,Not a single star in sight, in the sea of ​​sadness
